## Usage Guide

This section provides step-by-step instructions for testing credential issuance and verification flows using the SWIYU Generic Test Wallet. The following usage guide, will use the Public Beta ID ([https://www.eid.admin.ch/en/public-beta-e](https://www.eid.admin.ch/en/public-beta-e)) for explanation.

### Browser CORS Configuration

To test the wallet locally with backend services, you may need to disable CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) security in your browser. This is **only recommended for development and testing purposes**.

**⚠️ Security Warning**: Disabling CORS should only be done on a separate browser profile used exclusively for development and testing. Never disable CORS on your main browser profile.

### For Google Chrome

```bash
google-chrome --disable-web-security --user-data-dir="/tmp/chrome_dev_session"
```

### Part 1: Beta ID Issuance

#### Request a Beta Credential

Navigate on the Beta Credential Service website [https://www.bcs.admin.ch/bcs-web/#/](https://www.bcs.admin.ch/bcs-web/#/) to the section **Request Beta ID** and click the **Request** button.

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_01.png)

Select a profil and click the **Request the issuing of a Beta-ID** button

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_02.png)

#### Extract Deeplink of the Beta Credential

Copy the image and paste it to any QR Code Scanner

Alternative : You can click on the QR Code with your mouse this will. The `Deeplink` will be copied in the clipboard

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_03.png)

#### Resolve the Credential in the Generic Test Wallet

You can now go to the Generic Test Wallet [https://swiyu-admin-ch.github.io/swiyu-generic-test-wallet/](https://swiyu-admin-ch.github.io/swiyu-generic-test-wallet/) without *Cors Security*, select an **Issuance V1** (Single Issuance) or **Issuance V2** (Batch Issuance). Paste the `Deeplink` and click on **Resolve**

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_05.png)

#### Check the result
The system should now go through several steps (Resolving Deeplink, Metadata, Token response, etc.). If everything is correct, green check marks will appear for all steps, and the Credential Details (e.g. as an SD-JWT) will be displayed at the bottom. Click on **Verify (V1)** (DIF) or **Verify (V2)** (DCQL) this redirects you to the verification tab.

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_06.png)

### Part 2: Beta ID Verification

#### Initiate a verification

Go back to the start page of the BCS website and click the **Verify** button in the **Verify Beta ID** section

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_07.png)

#### Select a verification process and extract the link
Choose a verification scenario (e.g. “Verify complete Beta ID”). A QR code will appear. Use the developer tools again (Network tab) to find the deep link for verification (often in the format swiyu-verify://... or as a link to a request object). (You can also extract the deeplink using the QR Code Image Extract deeplink from QR Code).

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_08.png)

#### Perform verification

In the local tool, switch to the “Verification V1 (DIF)” tab. Paste the extracted deep link (starting with swiyu-verify://..., including request_uri) into the input field and click “Resolve”.

swiyu-verify://?client_id=did:tdw:QmPEZPhDFR4nEYSFK5bMnvECqdpf1tPTPJuWs9QrMjCumw:identifier-reg.trust-infra.swiyu-int.admin.ch:api:v1:did:9a5559f0-b81c-4368-a170-e7b4ae424527&request_uri=

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_09.png)

#### Check verification result
The tool should resolve the request (e.g. “Resolving Deeplink”, “Required Claims”, etc.) with green check marks.

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_10.png)

#### Completion
The view on the BCS website should update and display the verification result. A successful test is confirmed by the message “The data of the Beta ID is authentic” with a green check mark, along with the personal data (e.g. name, date of birth).

![Demo](./docs/screenshots/screenshot_11.png)

### Extracting Deeplinks from QR Codes

#### Paste QR Code in QR Code Scanner
You can use the https://qrcoderaptor.com to paste the screenshotted QR Code by clicking on “Request Beta ID” button, this will display the needed deeplink that you can copy on “Copy” button.
